Legal Calculus 4.5 — Enhanced Modules — Module 42
📘 Legal Calculus — Module 42

TRO vs. PI — Same Factors, Different Urgency

⚖️ Core Message

Know when to ask for a TRO and when to proceed to a preliminary injunction (PI).
📖 Lesson Content

1. TRO: ex parte only with Rule 65(b) specifics; certify notice efforts.
2. PI: adversarial; plan evidentiary showings and limited testimony.
3. Both require Winter factors; tailor proof to irreparable harm and timing.
4. Always attach a short proposed order tailored to TRO/PI.
📝 Assignment

Prepare a side‑by‑side TRO/PI checklist with Rule 65 requirements and proof plan.
✅ Model Response

CHECKLIST (excerpt)

TRO: Notice certification; immediate harm facts; proposed order.

PI: Hearing request; witness list; exhibit index; findings template.

 

💡 Reflection Summary

Speed changes format; factors stay the same.
🎨 Visual Concept

Two columns labeled TRO and PI under a single 'Winter' banner.
